This page gives you guidance on how to stay safely in Seychelles as a visitor, if you are unable to return to the UK.
Everyone should comply with the measures put in place in Seychelles to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
Moving around in Seychelles
The Seychellios authorities introduced a lockdown from 9 April. From 4 May, restrictions on movement in Seychelles have eased, but some restrictions remain in place until further notice.
Restaurants and shops may open again, but must close at 8pm. Bars and clubs are to remain closed until further notice. People may return to work, but the prohibition of public assemblies and public events continues. People are also prohibited from gathering in groups of more than 4 until further notice. Parties and beach gatherings are not allowed. House parties, which include any person from outside the immediate household, are prohibited.
Restrictions are enforceable by law and can change at short notice. You should consult the Department of Health in Seychelles for further information and monitor local media for the latest developments.
